			<div type="bibliography">
				<!--ASI 1926-27, 178-80, 200-1. — ASB 1939, 12-22. — PR, 25-33. — PPPB I, 139. — Than Hswe 1991; 1992. — Falk 1997. — Stargardt 2000: 22, 24-7.-->
				<!--[Todo: markup citedRange elements if necessary]-->
				<p>The discovery of excerpts in Pali from the Abhidhamma and Vinaya inscribed on 20 gold leaves (in the style of palm-leaf manuscripts) was first reported in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ASI"/><citedRange>1926-27: 178-80, 200-1</citedRange></bibl>. The inscription was carefully edited by Lu Pe Win in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ASB"/><citedRange>1939: 12-22</citedRange></bibl>. A complete Burmese transcription appears in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ThaMyat1963_01"/><citedRange>25-33</citedRange></bibl>. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Luce1985_01"/><citedRange>I, 139</citedRange></bibl>, provides an overview and a summary of earlier literature. <bibl><ptr target="bib:ThanHswe1992_01"/></bibl> is a study of the script used for the inscription. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Falk1997_01"/></bibl> provides a Romanized transliteration with notes. Finally, <bibl><ptr target="bib:Stargardt2000_01"/><citedRange>22, 24-7</citedRange></bibl>, includes a detailed description of “The Golden Pali Text” with commentary. Re-edited here from published photographs.</p>
